Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Director Hazelton , BC Description Position: Library Director (Chief Librarian) for the Hazelton District Public Library Location: Hazelton, British Columbia Application Deadline: November 15, 2024 About the Hazelton District Public Library: (HDPL) HDPL is located on the bank of the Skeena River in the Village of Hazelton. The HDPL provides services to a number of communities covering a large geographic area often referred to as the “Upper Skeena" or "the Hazelton’s”. Approximate population served is 6444 people. The HDPL is a welcoming space for all where services are free of charge. We are a source of education, entertainment and a much-needed access point to information and internet services in our rural area. Position Summary The Hazelton District Public Library board of trustees is looking for a new, permanent Library Director due to a retirement.The Library Director;will provide vision and leadership for the successful delivery of public services in the Hazelton area.will be responsible for overseeing all aspects of library management, ensuring that services are delivered in alignment with the directives of the Board and the needs of our diverse community.will play a crucial role in executing the board’s Vision of promoting literacy, free access to information, and public engagement in a safe and inclusive environment.will be dedicated to enhancing the lives of our community members through prudent selection of resources, innovative programming, and effective outreach. Key Responsibilities Governance Finance Personnel Management Community Relations and Collaboration Programs and Services Collection Development Qualifications Master’s Degree in Library and Information Studies would be ideal, however related Education and Work Experience will be considered. Excellent written and verbal communication skills. Proficient computer skills. Strong conflict resolution and problem-solving abilities. Administrative and supervisory experience. Commitment to patron service and community engagement. Hourly Rate: The Hourly Rate for this position ranges from $25.00 to $30.00 per hour depending on qualifications and experience. Average week is 30 hours. How to Apply Interested candidates are invited to submit their resume and cover letter via email to braunwyn@citywest.ca on or before November 15, 2024. A detailed Job Description is available on our website: https://hazelton.bc.libraries.coop/library-information/job-opportunities/library-director-chief-librarian-position/ We thank all applicants for their interest; however, only short-listed applicants will be contacted. Compensation $25.00 to $30.00 per hour Closes: 15 November, 2024 Hazelton District Public Library Hazelton , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
