Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Director, Innovation &amp; Integration Oakville , ON Description Employment Status: Permanent Full-time (Non-Union) Primary Location: Central Branch Alternate Locations: This role will be required to travel to all site locations. As well, this role will have the opportunity to work from home (WFH) based on operational requirements.Hours: 35 hours per week which consists of regular business hours with occasional evenings and/or weekend shifts.Reporting to the Chief Executive Officer (CEO), the Director, Innovation &amp; Integration is a key member of the Executive Management Team responsible for providing strategic and operational leadership for corporate departments which may include Collection Development, Technology including web services, Capital Planning, Assessment &amp; Research, Marketing and Communications, Program Development and Community Engagement and Development including capital funds. In collaboration with the Director, Customer Experience and the senior management team, this position supports the CEO in leading the evaluation and reporting of the strategic plan objectives. The Director, Innovation &amp; Integration is responsible for providing leadership in the overall management and delivery of innovative library services, collaborative service implementation through systemwide teams and staff engagement. They lead and coach direct and indirect reports across multiple portfolios. This position also manages the development and implementation of a robust metrics and measurement/assessment process for both public and corporate functions at OPL.Oakville Public Library employees support and work within the policies and framework of the Library corporate culture as embodied in the Vision and Mission Statements, Values, Strategic Pillars, and the Canadian Federation of Library Associations’ position statements on Intellectual Freedom and Diversity and Inclusion, with particular emphasis on providing excellent customer service. What you'll doStrategic Leadership• As a member of the Executive Management Team, and in collaboration with the Board of Directors, contribute to developing and evaluating OPL’s strategic plan, work plan and objectives, operating and capital budgets, policies, and other strategic initiatives, ensuring effective change leadership and staff engagement processes• Provide leadership in identifying, analyzing, and prioritizing opportunities for improving or enhancing library service, guiding the development of innovative customer-oriented programs and services • Collaborate with the Director, Customer Experience in the implementation of new customer experience initiatives focused on improving customer service and experience and/or business processes focused on improving workflow, efficiency, or costs• Sponsor and champion major system-wide projects, report results and evaluate work plan initiatives as assigned, including leading department managers in implementing and evaluating system-wide goals and annual work plan actions• Oversee the planning, budgeting, and execution of capital projects (including facilities), ensuring alignment with the organization's mission, timely completion, and efficient use of resources• Support the CEO by acting as a strategic and technical resource in providing information and advice to the Board of Directors, as required and as appropriate• Work collaboratively across OPL, provide leadership of the overall planning, development, analysis, implementation and strategic management for assigned service areas• Establish and maintain strong relationships with the Executive Management Team to ensure their needs are understood• Attend Library Board meetings as required and provide advice and support as requiredOperational Leadership• Ensure excellence in the development of services and programs through research and development in support of OPL’s strategic directions and work plan• Manage large and complex budgets, conducting the financial affairs of the Library within approved budgets and effectively deploying library resources to meet strategic goals and objectives• Oversee the development and implementation of various departmental strategies including support for capital fund campaigns• In partnership with the Town of Oakville’s Information Technology Services department, provide strategic and operational leadership and oversight in the development of OPL’s information technology strategy and roadmap, including an effective data governance framework, ongoing maintenance and updating of information systems and infrastructure, and appropriate IT capital budget planning and allocationAssessment and Reporting• Plan, Assess and Research, ensuring OPL continues to develop, evaluate and measure focused priorities and strategies in an evidence-based approach, providing guidance and leadership of the Library’s metrics and measurement process and framework• Guide the creation and implementation of an organizational measurement framework and related processes, including the analysis of statistical operating results and Key Performance Indicators relative to objectives and strategic goals• Oversee the development and implementation of a robust assessment and reporting program including analytics and progress reporting for OPL Strategic Plan• Lead the analysis of statistical operating results and KPI’s relative to established strategies and objectivesPeople Leadership• Provide leadership to a team of approximately 5 direct reports, and 25 indirect reports, across multiple portfolios which include Marketing &amp; Communications, Community Engagement and Fund Development, Technology, Program Development, Collections Development• Nurture a learning environment with excellent facilitation and team-building skills• Provide leadership and facilitate strong collaboration across the library system as well as key partners such as the Town of Oakville and Region of Halton• Guide the development of direct reports and the extended management team• Coach and mentor leaders and staff for performance, retention, and engagement• Review staffing requirements to ensure OPL’s goals and objectives are achieved• Evaluate, recruit, and select staff that have the right competencies, technical skills, and personal abilities• Ensure all staff receive the appropriate onboarding, orientation, training and development, as well as ongoing performance evaluationsCommunity Engagement• Ensure effective and engaging community consultation or information sessions are held regarding new/renovated capital projects, capital and other fundraising initiatives, business and strategic planning and other matters of key importance to the communities • Advocate and appropriately position OPL by representing the Library in a broad range of settings and interactions with decision-makers, representatives of the library community, Town of Oakville, Region of Halton, provincial, municipal and national elected officials, the broader Oakville community and other OPL partnersYour experience and educational background• Bachelor’s Degree in a related field • Masters of Library Sciences (MLIS) or Information Studies from an accredited institution and/or a graduate degree in public administration is an asset.• 3 -5 years at a senior management level• Project management designation is an asset• Capital Planning experience is an asset• Experience working in a unionized environment• Proven skills in all aspects of supervisor including team leadership, training, hiring, evaluating, coaching and motivating staff• Demonstrated knowledge and experience in the principles and practices of accounting, budgeting and financial planningWho are we? Oakville Public Library strives to fulfill our mission of cultivating discovery and creativity in every phase of life. We are focused on exceptional customer service to meet the needs of the children, youth, adults, and seniors utilizing our physical or online services. We continue to be agile in our mandate to meet the needs of the residents of Oakville. What's it like to work at Oakville Public Library? It's challenging, stimulating, and hugely rewarding. Our positions offer tremendous diversity and excellent opportunities for professional growth. Every day, we commit to providing access to tangible resources and programs that inspire, encourage, and provoke thought for the residents of Oakville.Applications will be accepted on-line at www.opl.on.ca in the current opportunities section no later than midnight on October 31, 2024.The Oakville Public Library is an equal opportunity employer and is pleased to accommodate individual needs in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act, 2005 (AODA) within our recruitment process upon request. If you require accommodation at any time throughout the recruitment process please contact Human Resources at oplhr@oakville.ca.A Security Clearance Check with Vulnerable Sector Screening will be required for all employees and volunteers of the Oakville Public Library. Successful applicants must submit the Security Checks (dated within the last six months) prior to or on the first day of employment.The Oakville Public Library endeavours to provide a safe environment for all its employees. We thank all applicants for their interest, however, only those candidates considered for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $130,868.13 - $153,962.50 Closes: 31 October, 2024 Oakville Public Library Oakville , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
