Knowledge of MLA, APA, and Chicago citation styles. Comfortable with library circulation services and procedures. Experience using an Integrated Library System. Extensive working experience with Microsoft Office suite, including Access, Excel, and Word. Excellent interpersonal and written/verbal communication skills. Friendly, and approachable, with a customer-service orientation. Able to exercise good judgment. Adaptable, flexible, and a team player. Able to work independently with minimal supervision. Knowledge of International Students and the challenges they face is an asset. HOURS OF WORK: On-call and scheduled shifts Monday to Saturday as needed. The bulk of work is performed during the 8th to 13th weeks of the semester (late October-early December).Some evening availability is required. COMPENSATION: In addition to working with an inclusive, progressive group of people, we offer an hourly gross salary of $29.08. APPLICATION PROCEDURE: Please submit your application, including a cover letter and resume, through our portal https://www.columbiacollege.ca/careers/ Please note that filling out the entire profile is not mandatory to upload the required resume and cover letter to the platform. For additional information about the application process, please check Columbia College Application Process Application Deadline: November 6, 2024 At Columbia College, we foster a culture of equity, diversity, and inclusion. The College invites and encourages applications from all qualified individuals, including groups traditionally underrepresented in employment, who may contribute to the further diversification of our Institution. We thank all applicants for their interest in the position; only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation 29.08/hour Closes: 6 November, 2024 Columbia College VANCOUVER , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
